## Reflection / Journaling Prompts

- Where do I currently rely most on position power, and where could I consciously shift toward relationship or inspirational power instead?
- Which direct report most needs me to build relationship power with them, and what’s one step I can take this week?
- How might consistent use of the Manager Tools Trinity change my team’s sense of Safety, Growth/Challenge, and Fulfillment over the next 3–6 months?

## Key Takeaways

- The Three Pillars describe the experience people need at work; the Power Triangle explains where your influence comes from.
- Senior, trusted leaders lean heavily on relationship and inspirational power, using position power sparingly and wisely.
- The Manager Tools Trinity—1on1s, Feedback, Coaching, Delegation—is a practical way to provide the pillars and grow the right kinds of power.
- Starting with better 1on1s is a high-leverage first step toward becoming the kind of leader who chooses to serve, not just to command.
